<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910813-0067</DOCNO><DOCID>910813-0067.</DOCID><HL>   Letters to the Editor:   Urgent Request</HL><DATE>08/13/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A17</SO><RE>EUROPE (EU)FRANCE (FR)NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)WESTERN EUROPE (WEU)</RE><LP>   Your July 22 &quot;Down the Toilet&quot; editorial poses aninteresting dilemma for urbanites subjected to persistentpanhandling. It has become easy to resist requests for a buckfor a sandwich or two bits for a cup of coffee, but how cananyone with an ounce of compassion (and an appreciation forthe demands of nature) turn down a plea for a quarter for theDecaux toilet?   Pat Brockenborough</LP><TEXT>   Paducah, Ky.</TEXT></DOC>